0201.Sinners fear not the pride of sin. The worthy dread the ill within.
0202.Since evil begets evil dire Fear ye evil more than fire.
0203.The wisest of the wise are those Who injure not even their foes.
0204.His ruin virtue plots who plans The ruin of another man's.
0205.Who makes poverty plea for ill Shall reduce himself poorer still.
0206.From wounding others let him refrain Who would from harm himself remain.
0207.Men may escape other foes and live But sin its deadly blow will give.
0208.Ruin follows who evil do As shadow follows as they go.
0209.Let none who loves himself at all Think of evil however small.
0210.He is secure, know ye, from ills Who slips not right path to do evils.
